<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>UNIVERSAL PRAYERS - SALMODY *</B></FONT></H2>
<H3><PRE>
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  Let us pray brothers and sisters,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    for the Holy Church of God,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    for his servant (N.), our Pope,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    for all the bishops, priests and deacons,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                               G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and for all the people of God:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    so that, by being participants of all the celestial gifts
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    we may be able to announce to this suffering world
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                              Em B7 Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    the Good News of Our Risen Lord.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Em      D   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  HEAR US, O LORD.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  Let us pray brothers and sisters for all the rulers
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and for all people who have constituted
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                    G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    as heads and leaders of the nations:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    so that wars may cease and division may disappear
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                    Em B7 Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and all peoples may live in your peace.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Em      D   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  HEAR US, O LORD.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  Let us pray for those who suffer
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">	 in body and spirit
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                 G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000"> 	 and for all the poor in the world:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    so that through the intervention of prophets
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    they may all receive the announcement
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    of salvation and life, the consolation of your Word,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                          Em B7 Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and communion of the faithful in your Church.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Em      D   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  HEAR US, O LORD.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    Let us pray for this holy assembly,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    that gathered in your name celebrates today,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    the Memorial of the death and resurrection
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">             G   
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    of your Son:  
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    so that the Lord may grant us all zeal
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    for the salvation of all peoples,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    love for those who suffer,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and the joy of proclaiming the Gospel
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                 Em B7 Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    to this generation.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Em      D   Em
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  HEAR US, O LORD.
</PRE></H3>
<H4><FONT COLOR="#000000">* The text above is proposed for learning the melody only and it is not</FONT></H4>
<H4><FONT COLOR="#000000">  meant to be used continually.</FONT></H4>
